============= Instructions =========================================================================
You can specify your own mod filters here to be used in Enhanced Mod Manager.

1. First specify the number of filters you are adding:
     <Row Tag="LOC_FF16_NUMOF_CUSTOM_FILTERS" Language="en_US">
	    <Text>3</Text> 
     </Row>

2. Each filter should have a tag with the following name: 
     - LOC_FF16_CUSTOM_FILTER_#
   Where the # is the number of the filter:
     - LOC_FF16_CUSTOM_FILTER_1, then LOC_FF16_CUSTOM_FILTER_2 and so on..

3. On the first line of the <Text> tag set your filter name followed by a semi-colon:
     - <Text>Test filter;
 
4. The lines below should then be a list of mod ID's of the mods you want in the filter. You can 
   find this in that mod's .modinfo file or on the mod details screen within Enhanced Mod Manager. 
   Don't worry about spaces, they will be removed later. However you'll need to add a comma between 
   each mod ID:
 
   <Text>Test Filter;
	  47dccacd-f1d0-4f25-bb02-deb2b528c833,
	  9e9923e5-6842-4e7d-97e7-c9a56a85cf03,
	  5fa339e0-1cef-4a63-abdb-549fadbd670d	  
   </Text>
   
5. Save and if all is configured correctly your filters should be available. 
=====================================================================================================
-->

